  "body": "This commit removed a note to Envify in the documentation:\nhttps://github.com/facebook/react/commit/39ac88595d0d89beb89ffd598d4a6de1f3b3fee8\n\nRelated to PR: https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/1793\n\nAs far as I understand, the devDependency of Envify for React is used to produce the distributable files react.js and react.min.js.\nIt seems to be used here: https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/master/grunt/config/browserify.js\n\nBut when using React with Browserify or Webpack, I suppose Envify is not run so it seems to me we should rather use Envify in this case.\n\nAm I right? If yes it would be probably a good idea to document this.\n",
